Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.17,0:00:04.15,720PCN,,0,0,0,,你要是在东部时间上午十点十一点左右用FR24看过北大西洋上空
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.17,0:00:04.15,720PEN,,0,0,0,,If you’ve ever looked at a flight tracker sometime around 10 or 11 pm eastern
Dialogue: 1,0:00:04.15,0:00:09.63,720PCN,,0,0,0,,你会注意到这些飞机都排好长队一路飞往欧洲
Dialogue: 2,0:00:04.15,0:00:09.63,720PEN,,0,0,0,,you might have noticed something—perfect lines of planes stretching all the way to Europe.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:09.63,0:00:14.32,720PCN,,0,0,0,,而它们只是每天横跨北大西洋的两千趟航班中的一部分
Dialogue: 2,0:00:09.63,0:00:14.32,720PEN,,0,0,0,,These are just some of the over 2,000 daily flights that cross the Northern Atlantic.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:14.32,0:00:20.60,720PCN,,0,0,0,,这么多航班可得管好。这是纽约到伦敦的直线距离
Dialogue: 2,0:00:14.32,0:00:20.60,720PEN,,0,0,0,,With so many flights, there just has to be organization. This is the most direct route from New York to London.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:20.60,0:00:24.88,720PCN,,0,0,0,,你可能以为是这才是“直线”，错咧
Dialogue: 2,0:00:20.60,0:00:24.88,720PEN,,0,0,0,,You may think it’s this, a straight line, but that straight line isn’t actually a straight line.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:25.96,0:00:30.35,720PCN,,0,0,0,,这条曲线是“直的”，因为甭管有些神棍怎么想，地球是圆的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:25.96,0:00:30.35,720PEN,,0,0,0,,This curved line is a straight line because, despite what some may think, the earth is curved.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:30.52,0:00:34.07,720PCN,,0,0,0,,纽约到伦敦可能没这么直观
Dialogue: 2,0:00:30.52,0:00:34.07,720PEN,,0,0,0,,From New York to London the curve you see on a flat map isn’t too extreme, but in
Dialogue: 1,0:00:34.07,0:00:38.28,720PCN,,0,0,0,,但长一点，比如纽约到曼谷，在地球表面的直线距离
Dialogue: 2,0:00:34.07,0:00:38.28,720PEN,,0,0,0,,the case of a longer flight, such as from New York to Bangkok, the most direct route
Dialogue: 1,0:00:38.28,0:00:44.92,720PCN,,0,0,0,,不是这条，而是这条，横穿北极点。从北极点俯视图看的话更明显
Dialogue: 2,0:00:38.28,0:00:44.92,720PEN,,0,0,0,,is not this, but this—straight over the North Pole. It makes more since if you look at a north-pole oriented map.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:44.92,0:00:47.67,720PCN,,0,0,0,,如果你从亚特兰大到伦敦画一条直线
Dialogue: 2,0:00:44.92,0:00:47.67,720PEN,,0,0,0,,If you draw the most direct route between Atlanta and London
Dialogue: 1,0:00:47.67,0:00:51.60,720PCN,,0,0,0,,你会看到这条线几乎经过了东海岸所有大型国际机场
Dialogue: 2,0:00:47.67,0:00:51.60,720PEN,,0,0,0,,you’ll see that it passes over every major east coast international airport.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:51.60,0:00:55.71,720PCN,,0,0,0,,说明亚特兰大的欧洲航班的路线和
Dialogue: 2,0:00:51.60,0:00:55.71,720PEN,,0,0,0,,That means that planes from Atlanta to Europe travel on the exact same route as planes from
Dialogue: 1,0:00:55.71,0:00:59.57,720PCN,,0,0,0,,从夏洛特、华盛顿、巴尔的摩、费城、纽约、波士顿的路线是一样的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:55.71,0:00:59.57,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Charlotte, Washington, Baltimore, Philadelphia, New York and Boston.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:59.57,0:01:05.95,720PCN,,0,0,0,,这些横跨大西洋的航班主要在东部时间晚上六点到八点起飞，一大早在欧洲降落
Dialogue: 2,0:00:59.57,0:01:05.95,720PEN,,0,0,0,,All these transatlantic planes typically leave between 6-8 pm Eastern to time their arrival for early morning in Europe.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:05.95,0:01:11.22,720PCN,,0,0,0,,说明同一路线、同时可能有上百架飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:01:05.95,0:01:11.22,720PEN,,0,0,0,,This means that there are potentially hundreds of planes all going the exact same route at the exact same time.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:11.47,0:01:14.47,720PCN,,0,0,0,,北大西洋上空还有“高速气流”
Dialogue: 2,0:01:11.47,0:01:14.47,720PEN,,0,0,0,,The North Atlantic also has something known as the Jet Stream.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:14.47,0:01:20.95,720PCN,,0,0,0,,当中的西风速度大约每小时110英里(177公里、96海里)，飞机借着它能省很多时间
Dialogue: 2,0:01:14.47,0:01:20.95,720PEN,,0,0,0,,These easterly winds average around 110 mph and if planes fly in them, they can cut hours of their travel time,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:20.95,0:01:26.60,720PCN,,0,0,0,,然而，这条风带最强范围只有160公里宽、5公里高
Dialogue: 2,0:01:20.95,0:01:26.60,720PEN,,0,0,0,,however, the winds are only strongest in a line three miles high (5 km) and 100 miles (160 km) wide.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:26.60,0:01:28.68,720PCN,,0,0,0,,这又压缩了航路间距
Dialogue: 2,0:01:26.60,0:01:28.68,720PEN,,0,0,0,,That further concentrates the flights.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:28.68,0:01:34.11,720PCN,,0,0,0,,平均算来，纽约飞伦敦要花6小时15分钟
Dialogue: 2,0:01:28.68,0:01:34.11,720PEN,,0,0,0,,On average, an eastbound transatlantic flight from New York to London takes about 6 hours and 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:34.11,0:01:38.22,720PCN,,0,0,0,,飞回来则要顶着气流，飞行时间超过7小时
Dialogue: 2,0:01:34.11,0:01:38.22,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Coming back against the jet stream, the same flight takes over 7 hours.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:38.22,0:01:43.32,720PCN,,0,0,0,,有时风还能更大，比如在2015年1月8日
Dialogue: 2,0:01:38.22,0:01:43.32,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, the winds can be even more active such as on January 8th, 2015 when British
Dialogue: 1,0:01:43.32,0:01:51.14,720PCN,,0,0,0,,英航114航班，纽约飞伦敦，只花了5小时16分钟，创造了新的民航亚音速客机的记录
Dialogue: 2,0:01:43.32,0:01:51.14,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Airways flight 114 flew from New York to London in only 5 hours and 16 minutes—a new record for a commercial subsonic plane.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:51.14,0:01:56.22,720PCN,,0,0,0,,当天高速气流时速超过每小时200英里(320公里、174海里)，那架波音777
Dialogue: 2,0:01:51.14,0:01:56.22,720PEN,,0,0,0,,On that day, the jet stream was blowing over 200 mph (320 km/h) and the Boeing 777 reached
Dialogue: 1,0:01:56.22,0:02:02.50,720PCN,,0,0,0,,(地速)达到了每小时745英里(1200公里，647海里)，只比地面静风音速慢25km/h
Dialogue: 2,0:01:56.22,0:02:02.50,720PEN,,0,0,0,,a speed of 745 mph (1200 km/h) —only 16 mph (25 km/h) below the sound barrier.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:02.50,0:02:06.98,720PCN,,0,0,0,,如果风能让飞机少飞一小时，波音777每小时耗油2700加仑(10200升)
Dialogue: 2,0:02:02.50,0:02:06.98,720PEN,,0,0,0,,So when winds can cut an hour off a flight and a 777 burns 2,700 gallons (10,200 liters)
Dialogue: 1,0:02:06.98,0:02:16.01,720PCN,,0,0,0,,航空燃油每加仑1.89美元，那就为航司省下5103美元，就看你在哪个区域飞了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:06.98,0:02:16.01,720PEN,,0,0,0,,of fuel per hour and jet fuel costs $1.89 per gallon, that’s a $5,103 difference between being in the right, and the wrong winds.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:16.01,0:02:18.14,720PCN,,0,0,0,,希望你能知道这点非常重要
Dialogue: 2,0:02:16.01,0:02:18.14,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Hopefully you now see why this is important.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:18.14,0:02:22.73,720PCN,,0,0,0,,同一航线上有这么多飞机，通常来说问题不大
Dialogue: 2,0:02:18.14,0:02:22.73,720PEN,,0,0,0,,So there are all these planes that are flying the exact same route, but usually that’s no problem.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:22.73,0:02:27.31,720PCN,,0,0,0,,北美最忙航线，纽约到芝加哥，每天100趟航班
Dialogue: 2,0:02:22.73,0:02:27.31,720PEN,,0,0,0,,The busiest route in North America, New York to Chicago, sees over 100 flights per day
Dialogue: 1,0:02:27.31,0:02:32.92,720PCN,,0,0,0,,早晚高峰每五分钟一趟，它们也是都飞直线
Dialogue: 2,0:02:27.31,0:02:32.92,720PEN,,0,0,0,,leaving as frequently as every five minutes during the morning and evening rush and these planes just fly the most efficient route.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:32.92,0:02:37.17,720PCN,,0,0,0,,飞之前，航线规划会和空管一起定好航线，在飞行中
Dialogue: 2,0:02:32.92,0:02:37.17,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Before the flight, route planners file a plan with air traffic control and during the flight
Dialogue: 1,0:02:37.17,0:02:42.34,720PCN,,0,0,0,,空管用一些办法引导飞机前后间距最小的时候只有5海里
Dialogue: 2,0:02:37.17,0:02:42.34,720PEN,,0,0,0,,they’re just directed by air traffic control in a way that keeps them 5 nautical miles from other planes.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:42.34,0:02:48.66,720PCN,,0,0,0,,纽约飞芝加哥与飞伦敦的区别在于，北大西洋上空没有雷达
Dialogue: 2,0:02:42.34,0:02:48.66,720PEN,,0,0,0,,The difference between New York to Chicago and New York to London is that, over the North Atlantic, there is no radar.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:48.66,0:02:55.87,720PCN,,0,0,0,,雷达只能覆盖到海岸边250英里远。但横跨大西洋要飞上千英里
Dialogue: 2,0:02:48.66,0:02:55.87,720PEN,,0,0,0,,You see, radar only extends about 250 miles offshore. Transatlantic planes can be more than a thousand miles from shore.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:55.87,0:03:01.17,720PCN,,0,0,0,,所以每天早上，位于纽芬兰岛甘德市的甘德空管中心
Dialogue: 2,0:02:55.87,0:03:01.17,720PEN,,0,0,0,,That’s why every morning, the route planners at Gander Air Traffic Control Center in Gander, Newfoundland
Dialogue: 1,0:03:01.17,0:03:03.30,720PCN,,0,0,0,,会发布当日的北大西洋航路
Dialogue: 2,0:03:01.17,0:03:03.30,720PEN,,0,0,0,,publish the days North Atlantic Tracks.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:03.56,0:03:07.45,720PCN,,0,0,0,,前一晚，每家要在第二天飞跃大西洋的航司
Dialogue: 2,0:03:03.56,0:03:07.45,720PEN,,0,0,0,,The night before, every airline that will fly across the atlantic the following day
Dialogue: 1,0:03:07.45,0:03:12.14,720PCN,,0,0,0,,向甘德提交一份“首选航路信息”，告诉他们航司最想沿着哪条航线飞
Dialogue: 2,0:03:07.45,0:03:12.14,720PEN,,0,0,0,,sends Gander a Preferred Route Message indicating what they think the best route will be.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:12.14,0:03:17.48,720PCN,,0,0,0,,多数情况，甘德中心会同意这些请求，然后设计十多条航路
Dialogue: 2,0:03:12.14,0:03:17.48,720PEN,,0,0,0,,For the most part, Gander center follows these requests and creates a set of 10 or so routes.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:17.48,0:03:21.70,720PCN,,0,0,0,,这些航路保证尽可能多的飞机沿着尽可能高效的路线飞往欧洲
Dialogue: 2,0:03:17.48,0:03:21.70,720PEN,,0,0,0,,These tracks attempt to get the most amount of planes on the most efficient route to Europe.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:21.70,0:03:26.54,720PCN,,0,0,0,,这些路线标记规则，从南往北数，最南边的代号Z，然后是Y
Dialogue: 2,0:03:21.70,0:03:26.54,720PEN,,0,0,0,,The tracks are labeled: Zulu being the southernmost route, Yankee being the second southernmost,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:26.54,0:03:31.37,720PCN,,0,0,0,,接着是X、W以此类推，接下来我举个例子
Dialogue: 2,0:03:26.54,0:03:31.37,720PEN,,0,0,0,,then Xray, then Whisky, and so on and so forth. Here’s how a flight on the tracks works.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:31.37,0:03:36.50,720PCN,,0,0,0,,不过提前说下，接下来要有点专业了。假如我们要从纽约飞巴黎
Dialogue: 2,0:03:31.37,0:03:36.50,720PEN,,0,0,0,,And I’ll warn you, this is when the video gets technical. Let’s say we’re going from New York to Paris.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:36.50,0:03:40.00,720PCN,,0,0,0,,预定起飞前半小时，机长向空管请求往加拿大纽芬兰飞
Dialogue: 2,0:03:36.50,0:03:40.00,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Around half an hour before scheduled departure, the captain talks to normal air traffic control
Dialogue: 1,0:03:40.00,0:03:42.76,720PCN,,0,0,0,,预定起飞前半小时，机长向空管请求往加拿大纽芬兰飞
Dialogue: 2,0:03:40.00,0:03:42.76,720PEN,,0,0,0,,to request clearance for the route up to around Newfoundland, Canada.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:42.76,0:03:46.20,720PCN,,0,0,0,,多数情况我们的请求得到许可，又过一会起飞了
Dialogue: 2,0:03:42.76,0:03:46.20,720PEN,,0,0,0,,In most cases clearance is given, and soon after we’ll take off.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:46.20,0:03:51.39,720PCN,,0,0,0,,等飞机快要飞过圣劳伦斯湾，飞行员开始请求TA想要的北大西洋航路
Dialogue: 2,0:03:46.20,0:03:51.39,720PEN,,0,0,0,,About when the plane crosses the Gulf of St Lawrence, the pilot will request the North Atlantic Track that he or she desires.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:51.39,0:03:55.25,720PCN,,0,0,0,,这是今日飞跃大西洋的路线信息
Dialogue: 2,0:03:51.39,0:03:55.25,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Here’s today’s message describing the day’s routes over the Atlantic.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:55.25,0:03:58.79,720PCN,,0,0,0,,机长看过后，决定请求路线W
Dialogue: 2,0:03:55.25,0:03:58.79,720PEN,,0,0,0,,After looking over this, the pilot decides to request track Whisky.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:58.79,0:04:03.25,720PCN,,0,0,0,,意思是目前我们要先飞RAFIN航点，即路线W的起始点
Dialogue: 2,0:03:58.79,0:04:03.25,720PEN,,0,0,0,,That means that, at least for now, we’ll head towards the RAFIN waypoint, our oceanic entry point.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:03.25,0:04:06.57,720PCN,,0,0,0,,航点就是用来导航的点
Dialogue: 2,0:04:03.25,0:04:06.57,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Waypoints are fixed spots that are used for flight navigation.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:06.57,0:04:11.82,720PCN,,0,0,0,,方便空管和飞行员在无线电里交流，因为说坐标的话太麻烦了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:06.57,0:04:11.82,720PEN,,0,0,0,,These are much easier for Air Traffic Control to communicate to pilots than map coordinates when speaking over radio.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:11.82,0:04:18.57,720PCN,,0,0,0,,有些航点名称很有意思，新罕布什尔州莱巴嫩北部有三个点连起来意思是汉堡、薯条
Dialogue: 2,0:04:11.82,0:04:18.57,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Occasionally you’ll see some creatively named waypoints. Just north of Lebanon, New Hampshire are HAMMM, BURGR, and FRYYS.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:18.83,0:04:23.50,720PCN,,0,0,0,,堪萨斯城机场进近上，你们自己看吧我都饿了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:18.83,0:04:23.50,720PEN,,0,0,0,,On approach to Kansas City Airport there’s SPICY BARBQ TERKY SMOKE RIBBS.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:23.50,0:04:27.55,720PCN,,0,0,0,,芝加哥两个航点名字是他们两个棒球队：芝加哥小熊队(Cubs)和芝加哥熊队(Bears)
Dialogue: 1,0:04:23.50,0:04:27.55,720PCN,,0,0,655,,这里YouTuber说错成波士顿 不过波士顿也有航点用他们的球队命名
Dialogue: 2,0:04:23.50,0:04:27.55,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Boston has two waypoints in support of their sports teams, the KUBBS and BEARS.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:27.55,0:04:32.45,720PCN,,0,0,0,,有的航点则很严肃。华盛顿里根国际机场北部进近
Dialogue: 2,0:04:27.55,0:04:32.45,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Some waypoint names are more somber. On the northern approach route to Washington Regan National Airport,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:32.45,0:04:38.94,720PCN,,0,0,0,,{\fs33}离911事件中撞五角大楼的地方只有几英里，航点连起来就是“我们永远不会忘记9月11日”
Dialogue: 2,0:04:32.45,0:04:38.94,720PEN,,0,0,0,,just miles away from where a plane hit the Pentagon on 9/11, the waypoints read WEEEE WLLLL NEVVR FORGT SEP11.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:38.94,0:04:43.88,720PCN,,0,0,95,,由于北大西洋航路每天都在变，NOTAM只给出北大西洋航路的起点和终点
Dialogue: 1,0:04:38.94,0:04:43.88,720PCN,,0,0,655,,NOTAM是英语“给飞行员通知”(Notice To Airmen)的缩写
Dialogue: 2,0:04:38.94,0:04:43.88,720PEN,,0,0,70,,Since the North Atlantic Tracks change every day, the NOTAM just gives entry and exit waypoints,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:43.88,0:04:45.92,720PCN,,0,0,95,,和中间的坐标
Dialogue: 2,0:04:43.88,0:04:45.92,720PEN,,0,0,70,,and then coordinates for the route in between.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:45.92,0:04:49.45,720PCN,,0,0,95,,而路线坐标是在飞机起飞前早已设定好的
Dialogue: 2,0:04:45.92,0:04:49.45,720PEN,,0,0,70,,Since the track coordinates are pre-programed into the autopilot before take-off, there’s
Dialogue: 1,0:04:49.45,0:04:52.79,720PCN,,0,0,0,,也就没必要给它们挨个起名字了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:49.45,0:04:52.79,720PEN,,0,0,0,,no reason to name them as waypoints since they won’t be given over radio.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:52.79,0:04:56.69,720PCN,,0,0,0,,在刚刚的例子里，我们请求路线W，多数情况下甘德
Dialogue: 2,0:04:52.79,0:04:56.69,720PEN,,0,0,0,,In the case of this flight, we’re REQUESTING track WHISKY and, more than likely, Gander
Dialogue: 1,0:04:56.69,0:05:00.47,720PCN,,0,0,0,,空管中心会允许，但也有些情况下他们会让我们走别的航路
Dialogue: 2,0:04:56.69,0:05:00.47,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Control Center will give permission, although, sometimes they’ll tell us to take a different track,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:00.47,0:05:04.32,720PCN,,0,0,0,,通常因为我们与其他飞机距离小于最小间隔
Dialogue: 2,0:05:00.47,0:05:04.32,720PEN,,0,0,0,,usually because we’re closer to another plane than the minimum separation distance.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:04.32,0:05:07.32,720PCN,,0,0,0,,因为在北大西洋上空知道飞机位置很难
Dialogue: 2,0:05:04.32,0:05:07.32,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Since it’s much more difficult to know where planes are over the North Atlantic,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:07.32,0:05:13.95,720PCN,,0,0,0,,{\fs32}所以他们间隔要求是15分钟——大约140英里(225公里、122海里)——远大于有雷达时的5海里
Dialogue: 2,0:05:07.32,0:05:13.95,720PEN,,0,0,0,,they're required to be 15 minutes separated—about 140 miles—rather than the normal 5 miles in areas with radar coverage.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:13.95,0:05:17.33,720PCN,,0,0,0,,假如我们获准了，我们就往RAFIN航点飞，然后确认
Dialogue: 2,0:05:13.95,0:05:17.33,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Assuming we’re granted clearance, we’ll head towards RAFIN waypoint and make sure
Dialogue: 1,0:05:17.33,0:05:20.63,720PCN,,0,0,0,,卫星通讯系统正常，然后检查
Dialogue: 2,0:05:17.33,0:05:20.63,720PEN,,0,0,0,,that our satellite communication systems are working, then we’ll check to see if the
Dialogue: 1,0:05:20.63,0:05:24.65,720PCN,,0,0,0,,高频无线电正常——这是其他通讯设备失效时的备份
Dialogue: 2,0:05:20.63,0:05:24.65,720PEN,,0,0,0,,High Frequency Radio is working—a backup in case other communications go down.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:24.65,0:05:28.65,720PCN,,0,0,0,,几分钟后，通过RAFIN点后，空管会说
Dialogue: 2,0:05:24.65,0:05:28.65,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Minutes later, just after passing RAFIN waypoint, the controller will say
Dialogue: 1,0:05:28.65,0:05:33.30,720PCN,,0,0,0,,“雷达服务终止，晚安”，然后我们就自己飞了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:28.65,0:05:33.30,720PEN,,0,0,0,,“radar services terminated, have a good night,” and then we’re on our own.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:33.30,0:05:38.77,720PCN,,0,0,0,,整条航路早已写进了自动驾驶，所以飞行员啥都不用干，等着就行
Dialogue: 2,0:05:33.30,0:05:38.77,720PEN,,0,0,0,,All the North Atlantic Tracks are preloaded onto autopilot, so there’s nothing really to do except wait.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:38.77,0:05:43.32,720PCN,,0,0,0,,过了西经30度，我们离欧洲越来越近了，进入Shanwick区域空域
Dialogue: 2,0:05:38.77,0:05:43.32,720PEN,,0,0,0,,When we we hit 30 west, we enter the Shanwick airspace approaching Western Europe.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:43.32,0:05:47.82,720PCN,,0,0,0,,无线电调到Shanwick的频率，再飞一小时到北大西洋航路终点——
Dialogue: 2,0:05:43.32,0:05:47.82,720PEN,,0,0,0,,We switch our radios to Shanwick’s frequency, then fly a few more hours to our Oceanic Exit
Dialogue: 1,0:05:47.82,0:05:53.12,720PCN,,0,0,0,,GUNSO航点——说明我们成功飞跃北大西洋了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:47.82,0:05:53.12,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Point—GUNSO waypoint—meaning we’ve successfully traversed the Northern Atlantic.
